12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
14 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1-702.1 of Title 63, unless
15 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
16 No public trust hospital license or main provider location under
17 a provider agreement with the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid
18 Services (CMS), as provided for under 42 C.F.R., Sections 489.1
19 through 489.18, shall be transferred from its current address to an
20 address greater than fifteen (15) miles away, if the public trust
21 hospital is located in a community with a population of fewer than
22 thirty thousand (30,000) residents, according to the latest Federal
23 Decennial Census. If a public trust hospital facility announces a
24 closure, before the closure of the facility, a mediator shall be
