1 appo inted. The municipality beneficiary of the public trust
2 hospital shall also appoint a mediator. The two mediators shall
3 appoint a mutually agreed-upon third mediator. The three mediators
4 shall agree upon a sales price for the hospital, in accordance with
5 appropriate due diligence and financial audits received from the
6 public trust hospital, if the hospital and the municipality cannot
7 agree without mediation. The hospital shall be transferred to the
8 beneficiary municipality if the beneficiary municipality is willing
9 to pay the agreed-upon purchase price set forth by the mediators and
10 has the appropriate staff identified to operate the hospital.
11 In the event the public trust hospital is sold to another
12 entity, the trustees of the hospital shall certify that they have
13 not entered into any agreement, formal or informal, with the
14 prospective owners of the hospital regarding any position, role, or
15 employment for themselves or their direct relatives, and they shall
16 also certify that they have not and will not receive any financial
17 benefit from the prospective owners, whether in-kind or otherwise.
18 In the event a public, third party, has been leasing the public
19 trust hospital and operating the public trust hospital under a
20 lease, upon termination of that lease, the hospital CMS provider
21 number shall revert back to the public trust hospital immediately
22 upon lease termination, in accordance with the provisions of 42
23 C.F.R., Section 489.18.
